nodes.title: 提示词文本

widgets_values:
一共生成了多少段分镜视频，就在上面source_images接上对应的【合并图像_n】，new_images接上对应的【分镜图像_n】。
例如：你跑了6段分镜，就分别接上【合并图像_6】和【分镜图像_6】。

--------------------------

The total number of storyboard video segments generated is indicated by appending the corresponding `[Merged Image_n]` to `source_images` and the corresponding `[Storyboard Image_n]` to `new_images`.

【输入方式】：参考图 + 文本描述  
【延展目标】：基于上一张图的画面风格、人物外形、光影氛围、镜头语言，生成下一张分镜图，使得剧情延续，在每一个分镜提示词结尾后增加一个空白的空行。
【提示词要求】：结合加载的图片，写出提示词描述，要求动作连贯，剧情合理。长符合动作的逻辑，提示词要简洁,并且有动感的运镜。如果图中没有人物则不需要描写人物。
输出时每一段文字是连续的，每一段提示词要重复一小段上一段提示词的结尾内容作为这一段提示词的起始内容，第一段提示词不需要重复上一段。提示词内没有特殊符号，没有多余的解释，每一段文字200个汉字以内，直接输出内容。

保持人物外观一致  
色调光影与参考图统一  
背景元素延续，不突变  
构图具备电影感（景别 / 光影 / 空间层次）

人物发色、身形不变  
服饰延续衔接，不跳变  
动作表情是上一个镜头的自然推进  
背景环境连续递进

高清画面  
电影级光影  
真实材质  
无噪点无畸变  
可作为下一张分镜生成基础

光源类型 为日光、人工光、月光、实用光、火光、荧光、阴天光、混合光、晴天光等
光线类型 可以描述为柔光、硬光、顶光、侧光、背光、底光、边缘光、剪影、低对比度、高对比度
时间段 白天、夜晚、黄昏、日落、黎明、日出。
景别 特写、近景、中景，中近景、中全景、全景、广角
描述构图类型 中心构图、平衡构图、侧重构图、对称构图、短边构图
镜头描述-镜头尺寸 中焦距、广角、长焦、望远、超广角-鱼眼
镜头描述-镜头角度 过肩角度、高角度、低角度、倾斜角度、航拍、俯视角度
镜头描述-镜头类型 单人镜头、双人镜头、三人镜头、群像镜头、定场镜头
色调 暖色调、冷色调、高饱和度、低饱和度等。
运动描述 跳舞、跑步、滑滑板、踢足球、网球、乒乓、滑雪、篮球、橄榄球、顶碗舞、侧手翻等。
人物情绪 愤怒、恐惧、高兴、悲伤、惊讶。
基础运镜 镜头推进、镜头拉远、镜头向右移动、镜头向左移动、 镜头上摇 高级运镜 手持镜头、复合运镜、跟随镜头、环绕运镜
风格化-视觉风格 毛毡风格、3D卡通、像素风格、木偶动画、3D游戏、黏土风格、二次元、水彩画、黑白动画、油画风格 风格化-特效镜头 移轴摄影、延时拍摄

widgets_values:
【输入方式】：参考图 + 文本描述  
【延展目标】：基于上一张图的画面风格、人物外形、光影氛围、镜头语言，生成下一张分镜图，使得剧情延续，每一段提示词之间要有差异。
【提示词要求说明】
请结合我已加载的图片进行提示词编写，展开后续的提示词描述，要求人物动作衔接自然，不要出现突然的不合理的动作转换，转身朝反方向走，不要出现转身，情节发展合理连贯。整体提示词需保持简洁，每一个分镜的提示词文字控制在 100 字以内。
第一个分镜的提示词必须在开头完整描写画面风格（2D风格、3D CG、动漫，二次元、2.5D、真实视频、超现实图像、水墨画、黏土等），人物发型，发色，眼睛颜色，服装，配饰设定以及人物的起始状态或动作，不要换行，再接着描述人物在第一个分镜中的具体动作。后面的分镜只需要描述画面风格以及该分镜中人物的动作行为，以及简单的描写场景或环境的变化，无需重复外观或服装设定。
提示词内容中不使用任何特殊符号，不添加多余解释，直接输出描述文本即可。在每一个分镜提示词结束后，需额外空一行作为分隔。

不要出现突然的不合理的动作转换，转身朝反方向走，不要出现转身，
nodes.title: 人物图反推模板

widgets_values:
[Input Method]: Reference Image + Text Description

[Extended Goal]: Based on the visual style, character appearance, lighting, and camera language of the previous image, generate the next storyboard to ensure plot continuity. Each cue should be distinct.

[Cue Requirements]: Please write cue text based on the images I have already loaded, expanding on subsequent cue descriptions. Character movements should flow naturally, avoiding sudden and illogical action transitions. For example, turning around and walking in the opposite direction should not involve turning around. The plot development should be logical and coherent. The overall cue text should be concise, with each storyboard cue text limited to 100 characters.

The cue text for the first storyboard must begin with a complete description of the visual style (2D style, 3D CG, anime, 2D, 2.5D, live-action video, surreal imagery, ink painting, clay modeling, etc.), character hairstyle, hair color, eye color, clothing, accessories, and the character's initial state or action. Do not use line breaks before continuing with a description of the character's specific actions in the first storyboard. The subsequent storyboards only need to describe the visual style and the characters' actions within that scene, along with a simple depiction of changes in the scene or environment. There's no need to repeat appearance or clothing details.

The cue text should not use any special symbols or add unnecessary explanations; simply output the descriptive text. After each storyboard cue text, add an extra blank line as a separator.

Avoid sudden and illogical action transitions; do not turn around to walk in the opposite direction.
nodes.title: Reverse deduction template for portrait images [English]

widgets_values:
[Input Method]: Reference Image + Text Description

[Extended Goal]: Based on the visual style, character appearance, lighting, and camera language of the previous image, generate the next storyboard image to ensure plot continuity. Add a blank line after the end of each storyboard cue.

[Cue Requirements]: Based on the loaded image, write a cue description that ensures smooth action and a logical plot. The cue should be logically consistent with the actions, concise, and include dynamic camera movement. If there are no characters in the image, character description is unnecessary.

Output: Each paragraph of text is continuous. Each cue paragraph should repeat a short section of the ending content of the previous paragraph as its starting point. The first paragraph does not need to repeat the previous paragraph. There should be no special symbols or unnecessary explanations within the cue. Each paragraph should be no more than 200 Chinese characters; output the content directly.

Maintain consistent character appearance.
Consistent color tone and lighting with the reference image.
Continued background elements, without abrupt changes.
Cinematic composition (shot size/lighting/spatial layering).

Unchanged hair color and body shape.
Continued and seamless clothing.
Natural progression of actions and expressions from the previous shot.
Continuous and progressive background environment.

High-definition image quality.
Cinematic lighting and shadow.
Realistic materials. No noise or distortion.
Can serve as a basis for generating the next storyboard.

Light source types: Sunlight, artificial light, moonlight, practical light, firelight, fluorescent light, cloudy light, mixed light, sunny light, etc.
Light type: Can be described as soft light, hard light, top light, side light, backlight, bottom light, edge light, silhouette, low contrast, high contrast.
Time period: Daytime, nighttime, dusk, sunset, dawn, sunrise. Shot Type: Close-up, Medium Shot, Medium Close-up, Medium Full Shot, Full Shot, Wide Angle

Composition Type: Central Composition, Balanced Composition, Side Composition, Symmetrical Composition, Short Side Composition

Lens Description - Lens Size: Medium Focal Length, Wide Angle, Telephoto, Telephoto, Ultra Wide Angle - Fisheye

Lens Description - Lens Angle: Over-the-shoulder Angle, High Angle, Low Angle, Tilt Angle, Aerial Shot, Top-Down Angle

Lens Description - Lens Type: Single-person Lens, Two-person Lens, Three-person Lens, Group Shot, Fixed-scene Lens

Color Tone: Warm Tone, Cool Tone, High Saturation, Low Saturation, etc.

Sports Description: Dancing, Running, Skateboarding, Soccer, Tennis, Table Tennis, Skiing, Basketball, Rugby, Bowling, Carabiner, etc.

Character Emotions: Anger, Fear, Happiness, Sadness, Surprise

Basic camera movements: camera zoom in, camera zoom out, camera pan to the right, camera pan to the left, camera tilt upwards. Advanced camera movements: handheld camera, composite camera movements, tracking camera, panning camera.
Stylized visual styles: felt style, 3D cartoon, pixel style, puppet animation, 3D game, claymation, anime, watercolor, black and white animation, oil painting style.
Stylized special effects: tilt-shift photography, time-lapse photography.
